-- Peru Stocks: Continental, Credicorp, Ferreyros, Relapasa
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-20T20:57:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/peru-stocks-atacocha-credicorp-ferreyros-intergroup.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.5 percent to 23,264.90. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.3 percent to 2,964.95.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, rose 1.9 percent to 1.06 soles after
crude advanced in  New York .  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, advanced 1.7 percent to $131.15 after U.S. and European
stocks rebounded, said Angel Alcala, a trader at Lima-based Juan
Magot y Asociados SAB. Total  car loans  rose 18 percent to $562
million through March, according to the Peruvian Banking
Association.  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of
 Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, gained 1.5 percent
to 6.60 soles.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of
Peru’s fourth-largest bank, climbed 1.2 percent to $32.40.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., rose 1.3 percent to 3 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
